class.description:
[AESContextGDRE] implements AES encryption and decryption for use inside [CustomDecryptor] implementations. It supports AES-128, AES-192, and AES-256 (key length 16, 24, or 32 bytes) and exposes ECB, CBC, and CFB modes - the last of which Godot's built-in [code]AESContext[/code] does not provide but is the mode Godot uses for encrypted PCK files (AES-256-CFB).
Input data must be a multiple of 16 bytes; pad the buffer before passing it to [method update].
[codeblock]
func decrypt_aes_cfb(data: PackedByteArray, key: PackedByteArray, iv: PackedByteArray) -> PackedByteArray:
    var ctx = AESContextGDRE.new()
    ctx.start(AESContextGDRE.MODE_CFB_DECRYPT, key, iv)
    var decrypted = ctx.update(data)
    ctx.finish()
    return decrypted
[/codeblock]
